es that fails to secure the rights of Iranians.  "We will not approve any agreement until we are certain that the rights of the Iranian people have been upheld," Ghalibaf said, in a video broadcast on state television.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/iran-chief-negotiator-says-no-deal-with-us-until-iranian-rights-secured/articleshow/131424022.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/iran-chief-negotiator-says-no-deal-with-us-until-iranian-rights-secured/articleshow/131424022.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-31T19:23:32+05:30</pubDate><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131424072,imgsize-447402.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Five Ebola patients recover in Congo as WHO opens new treatment centre]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131423211.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Five patients infected with a rare Ebola strain have recovered in the Democratic Republic of Congo, with four set for discharge from a new treatment center. This marks the first documented recovery from the Bundibugyo strain, as the WHO urges early medical attention amidst community resistance and a rapidly spreading outbreak.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/five-patients-recover-from-ebola-in-congo-as-who-launches-new-treatment-centre/articleshow/131423211.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/five-patients-recover-from-ebola-in-congo-as-who-launches-new-treatment-centre/articleshow/131423211.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-31T18:08:32+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131423203,imgsize-681935.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[22-year-old Parth Patel arrested in US after scamming Illinois resident out of $40,000]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131423051.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/22-year-old-parth-patel-arrested-in-us-after-scamming-illinois-resident-out-of-40000-by-posing-as-fbi-agent/articleshow/131423051.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/22-year-old-parth-patel-arrested-in-us-after-scamming-illinois-resident-out-of-40000-by-posing-as-fbi-agent/articleshow/131423051.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-31T18:04:29+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131423138,imgsize-37322.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Nepal PM calls for dialogue with India to resolve border issues, seeks UK's involvement in talks]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131422526.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Nepal's Prime Minister Balendra Shah proposed resolving border disputes with India through dialogue and suggested involving the UK, citing its historical role in defining regional borders. He emphasized negotiations and diplomatic efforts, noting that Nepal has exchanged notes with India to examine historical and geographical records concerning disputed territories.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/nepal-pm-calls-for-dialogue-with-india-to-resolve-border-issues-seeks-uks-involvement-in-talks/articleshow/131422526.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/nepal-pm-calls-for-dialogue-with-india-to-resolve-border-issues-seeks-uks-involvement-in-talks/articleshow/131422526.cms]]></gu